SETUP PROCESS

    > Setup or get access to a MySQL database. 

	> Create 'auth_details.php' in /php folder, and set variables $hostname, $user, $pass, $dbname.
	
    > Get a flat file with database meta information with the format 
		
			"database name|table name|column name" 
	  
	  One column symbolises one column, belonging to table name and database name.
	  
	> Move the flat file to /data folder.
	  
	> Set the flat file name in $filename, in /php/update_read_flatfile.php.
	
	> If the flat file delimiter is something other than "|", change this in $delimiter in /update_read_flatfile.php.
	
	> Run /php/creation_create_db.php to create the necessary tables in the database. 

	> Run /php/update_main.php to populate the database.
	
	> Done!
		